Configure xclock in Oracle Linux 8 for Display Graphical user interface

Error :

bash: xclock: command not found

Xclock is not working in Linux 8

1. Prerequisites

a. login as root user in putty terminal or use the command in the prompt

su -

b.  Check OS Version

uname -a

Example :
[root@servername ~]# uname -a
Linux servername 5.4.17-2136.327.2.el8uek.x86_64 #2 SMP Fri Jan 5 14:55:52 PST 2024 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux

2. Check RPM exists if the output is empty then install RPM

rpm -qa xorg-x11-apps

3. Install RPM

Use company company-authorized proxy if you are VPN or firewall restriction

export https_proxy=www-proxy-servername.ind.servername.com:80
export http_proxy=www-proxy-servername.ind.servername.com:80

4. dnf config-manager --enable ol8_codeready_builder

5. dnf install xorg-x11-apps 
